## Description {#details}

<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/vppredinstphirecipe">VPPredInstPHIRecipe</a> is a recipe for generating the phi nodes needed when control converges back from a Branch-on-Mask.

The phi nodes are needed in order to merge values that are set under such a branch and feed their uses. The phi nodes can be scalar or vector depending on the users of the value. This recipe works in concert with <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/vpbranchonmaskrecipe">VPBranchOnMaskRecipe</a>.
